OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F435A1775235955
OL,3,CLocals angered by fly-tipping on
OL,4,Cpopular dog walking route in Somerset
OL,6,FA lengthy section of footpath in
OL,7,FSomerset was made impassable after it
OL,8,Fcovered with flytipped waste,
OL,9,Fincluding roof tiles, mattresses and
OL,10,Fchildren's toys.
OL,12,FKitty Fleming was walking her dog in
OL,13,FPilton when she found her path blocked
OL,14,Fby the waste on Tuesday morning.
OL,16,FThe rubbish was dumped between Copse
OL,17,FLane and Mount Pleasant and stretched
OL,18,Fmore than ten metres, covering the
OL,19,Fwhole of the path, which is popular
OL,20,Fwith dog walkers.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G1/4
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
